# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if the
#   project is decimal-bound. See:
#   https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv#simple-python-version-management
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different platforms or sub-versions,
#   Pipfile.lock might be conflictual.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains the resolved dependencies, which is adviseable to commit.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock contains the resolved dependencies, which is adviseable to commit.
# pdm.lock

# PEP 582; project local packages (e.g. pdm)
__pypackages__/

